rComments: He's a nice guy and he means well but the tests do not reflect the course material in the least (mostly analysis not math). Midterm average was a 50 before he curved it but somehow he was very proud of this.. He's very approachable and willing to answer questions but a lot of the time his powerpoints have mistakes in them.
It's a tough class, and he means well, but his lectures are dry. He gives you many assignments so it is very difficult to fail the class.
Prof Coulombe was excellent. He was very clear when explaining and made sure students understood. He also bell curves everyones marks up.

Prof knows is stuff. Professional at what he does but he is not that clear for psychology students trying to learn statistics. Prepare the other side of your brain, cause this class is a totally different ball game with this prof.

He is kind enough, but he is completely oblivious to students' struggles. Stats is rarely fun, but his 3 hour class really tested my patience even though I'm a hardworking and good student. It was really stressful and confusing most of the time. On the flip side, he is flexible and bell curves results so that half the class doesn't fail.

Very nice prof. As opposed to what the other reviewer said, I don't think this class was tough, it's just that most psy. students are too lazy to have an in-depth look into statistics. Material was pretty easy overall and prof very available to answer any questions. Nice man as well.

Students were told the exam would be easy if well prepared and would only take about an hour and a half to complete, after two and a half hours 3/4 of the class was still there. Exams were incredibly difficult and we were not well prepared for it. Spent very little time on material that was most present in the exam.
